    dc:date "2015" ;
    dc:title "Review of the family Anthogonidae (Diplopoda, Chordeumatida), with descriptions of three new species from the Balkan Peninsula" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.240309>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.240297>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.240300>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.240302>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.240299>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.240301> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.240309>
    dc:description "FIGURES 85 – 88. Balkan anthogonids in their natural habitats. 85: Egonpretneria sp., female from the Ponor na Štirovači Cave, Velebit Mt. (photo by A. Kirin); 86: Macrochaetosoma troglomontanum Absolon & Lang, 1933, male from the Kuna Špilja Cave, Biokovo (photo by R. Ozimec); 87: Haasia likana (Strasser, 1966), female from the Manita Peć Cave, Velebit Mt. (photo by T. Dražina); 88: Haasia stenopodium (Strasser, 1966), female from the Lukina Jama Pit, Velebit Mt. (photo by M. Pavlek). Without scale. Size of specimens and ratios between sizes of specimens are not real." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/240309/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.240297>
    dc:description "FIGURES 19 – 22. Haasia jalzici sp. n., paratype male from the Ponor Sušik Cave, Gorski Kotar. 19: body segments XIV and XV, dorsal view; 20: macrochaetal knobs of body segment XV; 21: scale-like structures of metazonite XV; 22: cross-section of body segment XV, posterior view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/240297/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.240300>
    dc:description "FIGURES 30 – 35. Haasia likana (Strasser, 1966), topotype male from the Pčelina Špilja Cave, Velebit Mt. 30: cross-section of body segments XV and XVI, posterior view; 31: body segments XV and XVI, postero-lateral view; 32: body segments XV and XVI, dorsal view; 33: middle area of metazonite XVI; 34: limbus of metazonite XVI; 35: prozonite XV, dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/240300/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.240302>
    dc:description "FIGURES 42 – 47. Haasia stenopodium (Strasser, 1966), male from the Klementina 21 Pit, Velebit Mt. 42: body segment XV, dorsal view; 43: body segment XV, lateral view; 44: cross-section of body segment XV, posterior view; 45 and 46: limbus of body segment XV; 47: leg pair VII." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/240302/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.240299>
    dc:description "FIGURES 27 – 29. Haasia jalzici sp. n., paratype male from the Ponor Sušik Cave, Gorski Kotar, gonopods. 27: anterior gonopods, anterior view; 28: anterior gonopods, posterior view; 29: posterior gonopods, anterior view. Designations: m: biramous medial sternal process, lcp: lateral coxal process. Scale line: 0.4 mm for Figs 27 and 28, 0.2 mm for Fig. 29." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/240299/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.240301>
    dc:description "FIGURES 36 – 41. Haasia likana (Strasser, 1966), topotype male from the Pčelina Špilja Cave, Velebit Mt., gonopodal block. 36: anterior view; 37: antero-lateral view; 38: lateral view; 39: postero-lateral view; 40: posterior view; 41: distal view. Designations: a: anterior coxal process; b: bristles apparatus; m: medial sternal process of posterior gonopods; lp: lateral syncoxal process; lcp: lateral coxal process of posterior gonopods; sco: syncoxite." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/240301/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

